# Omega Website Design System

Every page and component on the Omega website must follow these conventions to maintain visual consistency.

## Card System

- **Default card**: Use `className="glass-card"` — frosted glass background with backdrop-blur, subtle border, hover lift. Never use raw bordered boxes or inline `backgroundColor`/`border` combos.
- **Featured card**: Use `className="glass-card gradient-border"` — adds an animated conic-gradient border via pseudo-element. Reserve for primary/featured items (e.g. the Boost product card).
- **Never** use `.omega-card` for new components (kept only for backward compatibility). Always use `.glass-card`.
- **Never** add per-card hover handlers for border/shadow/transform. The `.glass-card` class handles all hover states globally.

## Section Structure

Every content section follows this pattern:

```
SectionLabel → Heading → Text (optional subtext) → Content (grid, cards, etc.)
```

- Wrap content in `StaggerReveal` for scroll-triggered entrance animations.
- Use `className="section-movement"` on every `<Section>` for consistent vertical padding and top border.
- Use `className="section-alt"` on alternating sections for subtle background differentiation.

## Typography

| Element | Font | Weight | Color |
|---|---|---|---|
| Headings | `var(--font-outfit)` | 300 (light) | `var(--gray-12)` |
| Body text | `var(--font-outfit)` | 400 | `var(--gray-11)` |
| Section labels | `var(--font-jetbrains-mono)` | 400 | `var(--gray-9)` |
| Card labels | `var(--font-jetbrains-mono)` | 400 | `var(--gray-10)` |
| Code / terminals | `var(--font-jetbrains-mono)` | 400 | `var(--gray-11)` |
| Secondary/muted | `var(--font-outfit)` | 400 | `var(--gray-10)` |

- Headings use `letterSpacing: "-0.03em"` and `lineHeight: 1.1`.
- Body text uses `lineHeight: 1.65` to `1.7`.
- Section labels are rendered via `SectionLabel` component — monospace, 11px, `[bracketed]`.

## Color Hierarchy

- `--gray-12`: Primary text, headings
- `--gray-11`: Body copy, readable paragraphs
- `--gray-10`: Secondary text, card labels, italic details
- `--gray-9`: Muted text, section labels, timestamps
- `--gray-8`: Decorative text, icons, large card numbers
- `--gray-6` / `--gray-5`: Borders, dividers (hover states brighten these)
- `--gray-4`: Default card borders, subtle separators
- `--gray-3`: Subtle backgrounds (section-alt)
- `--gray-2`: Card backgrounds (glass-card base)

## Animation

- **Brand easing**: `[0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]` — use `BRAND_EASING` from `@/lib/constants`. In Framer Motion, always cast as `[number, number, number, number]`.
- **Stagger reveals**: Use `StaggerReveal` with `staggerChildren={0.06}` to `{0.1}` and `duration={0.5}`.
- **Float**: Use `className="float"` for gentle 3px bob animation (hero omega, decorative elements).
- **Shimmer**: Use `className="shimmer-badge"` for slowly shimmering text (e.g. "AVAILABLE" badge).
- **Stat glow**: Use `className="stat-glow"` for subtle text-shadow on large stat numbers.
- **Pulse arrow**: Use `className="pulse-arrow"` for animated directional arrows.
- **Reduced motion**: Always respect `useReducedMotion()` from Framer Motion. Provide static fallbacks.

## Component Rules

- Use Radix Theme components (`Box`, `Flex`, `Grid`, `Text`, `Heading`, `Button`, `Section`, `Container`, etc.) for all layout and typography. See the `radix-themes.mdc` rule.
- Never use raw `<div>`, `<p>`, `<h1>`, `<a>`, `<button>` when a Radix equivalent exists.
- Use `Box asChild` with semantic elements (`<span>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`) when you need the HTML tag.
- `InstallTabs` for tabbed terminal displays. `AnimatedTerminal` for single terminal blocks.
- `AnimatedStatBlock` for large stat numbers with intersection-observer-triggered animation.

## File Organization

- Sections live in `components/sections/` — one file per homepage section.
- Reusable UI primitives live in `components/ui/`.
- Layout components (nav, footer) live in `components/layout/`.
- Constants (easing, durations, offsets) live in `lib/constants.ts`.
